<ol>
<li>'''''Brackets:''''' choose one of: 
*'''bra''' (for a bra vector), 
*'''ket''' (for a ket vector),
*'''bra-ket''' (for the [[Bra–ket notation#Inner products and bras|inner product]]), or
<li>'''''Symbol 1:'''''
*if 1 is set to ''bra'' or ''ket'': enter the first symbol for the bra or ket, 
*if 1 is set to ''bra-ket'': enter the symbol for the ''bra'' part of the inner product</li>
<li>'''''Symbol 2:'''''
*if 1 is set to ''bra'' or ''ket'': this parameter is not needed.
*if 1 is set to ''bra-ket'': enter the symbol for the ''ket'' part of the inner product</li>
</ol>

If 1 is set to ''bra-ket'', the symbols are entered in the order they are read, left to right. The symbols can of course be '''bold''', ''italic'', <u>underlined</u>, any [[unicode]] symbol, etc. 

==Examples==

;Ket

A ket can be written: {{braket|ket|ψ}}, that is <code><nowiki>{{braket|ket|ψ}}</nowiki></code>.

Using {{tl|math}}, a ket can be written: {{math|{{braket|ket|ψ}}}}, that is <code><nowiki>{{math|{{braket|ket|ψ}}}}</nowiki></code>.

;Bra

A bra can be written: {{braket|bra|ψ}} = {{braket|ket|ψ}}<sup>†</sup>, that is <code><nowiki>{{braket|bra|ψ}} = {{braket|ket|ψ}}<sup>†</sup></nowiki></code>.

Using {{tl|math}}, a bra can be written: {{math|{{braket|bra|ψ}} {{=}} {{braket|ket|ψ}}<sup>†</sup>}}, that is <code><nowiki>{{math|{{braket|bra|ψ}} {{=}} {{braket|ket|ψ}}<sup>†</sup>}}</nowiki></code>.

;Bra-ket

The [[Bra–ket notation#Inner products and bras|inner product]] of the kets {{braket|ket|ξ}} and {{braket|ket|ψ}} can be written: {{braket|bra-ket|ψ|ξ}} = {{braket|bra-ket|ξ|ψ}}<sup>†</sup>, that is <code><nowiki>{{braket|bra-ket|ψ|ξ}} = {{braket|bra-ket|ξ|ψ}}<sup>†</sup></nowiki></code>.

Using {{tl|math}}, the inner product of the kets {{math|{{braket|ket|ξ}}}} and {{math|{{braket|ket|ψ}}}} can be written: {{math|{{braket|bra-ket|ψ|ξ}} {{=}} {{braket|bra-ket|ξ|ψ}}<sup>†</sup>}}, that is <code><nowiki>{{math|{{braket|bra-ket|ψ|ξ}} {{=}} {{braket|bra-ket|ξ|ψ}}<sup>†</sup>}}</nowiki></code>.

;Outer products

The [[Bra–ket notation#Outer products|outer product]] of the kets {{braket|ket|ξ}} and {{braket|ket|ψ}} can be written: {{braket|ket|ψ}}{{braket|bra|ξ}} = [{{braket|ket|ξ}}{{braket|bra|ψ}}]<sup>†</sup>, that is <code><nowiki>{{braket|ket|ψ}}{{braket|bra|ξ}} = [{{braket|ket|ξ}}{{braket|bra|ψ}}]<sup>†</sup></nowiki></code>.

Using {{tl|math}}, the outer product of the kets {{math|{{braket|ket|ξ}}}} and {{math|{{braket|ket|ψ}}}} can be written: {{math|{{braket|ket|ψ}}{{braket|bra|ξ}} {{=}} [{{braket|ket|ξ}}{{braket|bra|ψ}}]<sup>†</sup>}}, that is <code><nowiki>{{braket|ket|ψ}}{{braket|bra|ξ}} {{=}} [{{braket|ket|ξ}}{{braket|bra|ψ}}]<sup>†</sup></nowiki></code>.

;Inner products including [[operator (physics)|operator]]s

The inner product of the kets {{braket|ket|ξ}} and ''Ĥ''{{braket|ket|ψ}} is written using a bra and ket seperatley between the operator (there is no third parameter for the operator symbol): 
:{{braket|bra|ψ}}''Ĥ''{{braket|ket|ξ}} = {{braket|bra|ξ}}''Ĥ''<sup>†</sup>{{braket|ket|ψ}}, 
that is 
:<code><nowiki>{{braket|bra|ψ}}''Ĥ''{{braket|ket|ξ}} = {{braket|bra|ξ}}''Ĥ''<sup>†</sup>{{braket|ket|ψ}}</nowiki></code>.

Using {{tl|math}}, the inner product of the kets {{math|{{braket|ket|ξ}}}} and {{math|''Ĥ''{{braket|ket|ψ}}}} is written using a bra and ket seperatley between the operator: 
:{{math|{{braket|bra|ψ}}''Ĥ''{{braket|ket|ξ}} {{=}} {{braket|bra|ξ}}''Ĥ''<sup>†</sup>{{braket|ket|ψ}}}}, 
that is 
:<code><nowiki>{{math|{{braket|bra|ψ}}''Ĥ''{{braket|ket|ξ}} {{=}} {{braket|bra|ξ}}''Ĥ''<sup>†</sup>{{braket|ket|ψ}}}}</nowiki></code>.

;[[Schrödinger equation]]: 
In wiki-markup rather than LaTeX:
:{{math|''iħ''{{sfrac|''d''|''dt''}}{{braket|ket|Ψ(''t'')}} {{=}} ''Ĥ''{{braket|ket|Ψ(''t'')}} ↔ −''iħ''{{braket|bra|Ψ(''t'')}}{{sfrac|''d''|''dt''}} {{=}} {{braket|bra|Ψ(''t'')}}''Ĥ''<sup>†</sup>}}
that is,
:<code><nowiki>{{math|''iħ''{{sfrac|''d''|''dt''}}{{braket|ket|Ψ(''t'')}} {{=}} ''Ĥ''{{braket|ket|Ψ(''t'')}} ↔ −''iħ''{{braket|bra|Ψ(''t'')}}{{sfrac|''d''|''dt''}} {{=}} {{braket|bra|Ψ(''t'')}}''Ĥ''<sup>†</sup>}}</nowiki></code>

;[[Bra–ket notation#Composite bras and kets|Tensor products]]:

The [[tensor product]] of the kets {{braket|ket|ξ}} and {{braket|ket|ψ}} is written using the ket mode only (there is no paramter for tensor products): 
:{{braket|ket|ξ}}{{braket|ket|ψ}} ≡ {{braket|ket|ξ}}&otimes;{{braket|ket|ψ}} ≡ {{braket|ket|ξ, ψ}},
that is 
:<code><nowiki>{{braket|ket|ξ}}{{braket|ket|ψ}} ≡ {{braket|ket|ξ}}&amp;otimes;{{braket|ket|ψ}} ≡ {{braket|ket|ξ, ψ}}</nowiki></code>.

Using {{tl|math}}, the tensor product of the kets {{math|{{braket|ket|ξ}}}} and {{math|{{braket|ket|ψ}}}} is written using the ket mode only: 
:{{math|{{braket|ket|ξ}}{{braket|ket|ψ}} ≡ {{braket|ket|ξ}}&otimes;{{braket|ket|ψ}} ≡ {{braket|ket|ξ, ψ}}}}, 
that is 
:<code><nowiki>{{math|{{braket|ket|ξ}}{{braket|ket|ψ}} ≡ {{braket|ket|ξ}}&amp;otimes;{{braket|ket|ψ}} ≡ {{braket|ket|ξ, ψ}}}}</nowiki></code>.

